<br>
They do have their uses, but it's mostly as taxi's to hate and sky and western wastes.  There are one or two fights where wizards can help out, but really, they're not essential for anything.  If the class was removed from the game, it wouldn't much effect balance or play.  This doesn't mean wizards can't contribute, it just means that every other class in the game contributes more and is more useful more of the time.<br>
<br>
All that said, if you like meditating, Wizard is the class for you -- I used to trade and /auc and /gu up a storm while med'ing.  Can't /auc here, but if you have a good guild that is wizard-tolerant, it could be a fun class for the right person.<br>
<br>
Oh, and another tidbit -- Teir-dahl can hide.  This means a Teir-dahl wizard can often go afk while med'ing and remain perfectly safe.  If you go wizard, Inky is best. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utukka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/10/02 4:54:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1071.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.atlantic.net/~tukka/hand.gif height=42 width=42></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well ..</span><hr size=1> Bjond, are you taking in to consideration the stuff Luclin brings to the table for post-50 wizards?  I'm not familiar with the high end game, but some of this Luclin stuff is looking pretty sweet for a wizard... Familiars, reduction in spell cast time, spell criticals, items which modify spell skills and meditation, ect. <p><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS">--Tukka</FONT><BR>
